  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Noodles Stall Associate",
  "description": "<ul><li>Role Overview: Join our friendly noodle stall team to deliver authentic, delicious noodles to our daily customers. We're looking for someone with a passion for food, good communication skills and the ability to thrive in a fast-pace environment. </li></ul><p>🔑 <strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare ingredients accurately to support smooth cooking operations</li><li>Cook noodles following established recipes to ensure consistent taste and quality</li><li>Greet customers warmly and take orders accurately to provide excellent service</li><li>Process payments and manage order queues efficiently to maintain customer flow</li><li>Clean and sanitize the stall and kitchen tools regularly to uphold food safety standards</li><li>Monitor ingredient stock levels and restock supplies as needed to avoid shortages</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Experience working in food preparation or customer service environments is preferred but not required</li><li>Ability to work effectively in a fast-paced environment while maintaining quality and safety standards</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Competitive salary range of $2,000 - $3,000/month depending on experience</li><li>Friendly and supportive team environment</li><li>14 days medical leave and 7 days annual leave as per MOM regulations</li><li>Public holiday compensation with off in-lieu provided</li><li>Staff meals provided daily</li><li>Working hours: 12-hour shifts on a rotating schedule, including weekends and public holidays</li><li>Locations: Bukit Batok, Bedok, or Chua Chu Kang</li><li>No prior experience required; on-the-job training will be provided for the right candidate</li><li>How to Apply: Please contact Sean +60187798559 via WhatsApp call/message to learn more and arrange an interview</li></ul>",
